<subSubSection lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="614" pageId="8" pageNumber="613" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="8.[677,1209,1648,1699]" lastBlockId="9.[113,646,1071,1122]" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="614" pageId="8" pageNumber="613">ETYMOLOGY. — From ancient Greek ιππΟς (horse) and ΚΡΗπίς (shoe), in order to highlight the presence of large horseshoe-shaped punctures on elytra. Noun in apposition.</paragraph>
